Edwin Pearce Christy (November 28, 1815 – May 21, 1862) was an American composer, singer, actor and stage producer.
He was born on November 28, 1815 in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania to Robert F. Christy and Ruth Wheaton.

Christy began his career as a minstrel in Buffalo, New York.
He toured upstate New York from 1843 to 1845.
In April 1846 Christy and his band of six performers began performing in New York City at Polmer's Opera House.
After performing at a benefit performance for Stephen Foster in Cincinnati, Ohio, on August 25, 1847, the group specialized in performances of Foster's works.
